      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "e.getMessage() can still return an empty string; many exceptions rely on the exception class to indicate the problem, e.g. NullPointerException, and have no message.\n\nEven when non-empty, the exception class provides context for the message, e.g. a class name without knowing it's a ClassNotFoundException is difficult to interpret.\n\nSimply log the entire exception with e.toString() instead of e.getMessage() to get the full description.",
